#### API Summary

#### Tournaments

The following API calls are used for leaderboards with *Tournaments* attached:

* [GetTournamentStatus](#capi-tournament-gettournamentstatus) - view the state of a tournament
* [JoinTournament](#capi-tournament-jointournament) - join the specified tournament
* [LeaveTournament](#capi-tournament-leavetournament) - abandon the tournament
* [PostTournamentScoreUTC](#capi-tournament-posttournamentscoreutc) - post a score to the tournament
* [PostTournamentScoreWithResultsUTC](#capi-tournament-posttournamentscorewithresultsutc) - post a score to the tournament, and return the updated standings 
* [PostTournamentScoreOnBehalfOf](#capi-tournament-posttournamentscoreonbehalfof) - post another player's score to the tournament
* [ViewCurrentReward](#capi-tournament-viewcurrentreward) - preview the expected reward for the player based on their current rank in the tournament.
* [ViewReward](#capi-tournament-viewreward) - view the player's reward for a completed tournament. 
* [ClaimTournamentReward](#capi-tournament-claimtournamentreward) - claim the player's reward for a completed tournament.

Use the standard <a href="#" onclick='window.navigateToTarget("#capi-leaderboard");'>Leaderboard Service</a> apis for retrieving player standings (i.e. <a href="#" onclick='window.navigateToTarget("#capi-leaderboard-getgloballeaderboardpage");'><code>GetGlobalLeaderboardPage</code></a>, <a href="#" onclick='window.navigateToTarget("#capi-leaderboard-getgloballeaderboardview");'><code>GetGlobalLeaderboardView</code></a>, etc.)


#### Divisions
The following API calls are specific to *Divisions*:

* [GetDivisionInfo](#capi-tournament-getdivisioninfo) - get info about the specified division set. Call instead of `GetTournamentStatus()` to retrieve the prize rules and scheduling status of a division.
* [JoinDivision](#capi-tournament-joindivision) - join a division set (will be assigned to an instance). Call instead of `JoinTournament()`.
* [LeaveDivisionInstance](#capi-tournament-leavedivisioninstance) - leave a division instance. Call instead of `LeaveTournament()`.
* [GetMyDivisions](#capi-tournament-getmydivisions) - retrieves a list of the division instances that player is/has recently participated in

[PostTournamentScore](#capi-tournament-posttournamentscore), [ViewCurrentReward](#capi-tournament-viewcurrentreward), [ViewReward](#capi-tournament-viewreward), and [ClaimTournamentReward](#capi-tournament-claimtournamentreward) all work as expected for divisions.


#### System calls
* [SysCreateTournamentTemplate](#capi-tournament-syscreatetournamenttemplate) - Creates a new tournament template.
* [SysReadTournamentTemplate](#capi-tournament-sysreadtournamenttemplate) - Read a specific tournament template by tournament code and version.
* [SysEditTournamentTemplate](#capi-tournament-sysedittournamenttemplate) - Changes an existing tournament template.
* [SysListTournamentTemplates](#capi-tournament-syslisttournamenttemplates) - Lists all tournament templates.
* [SysDeleteTournamentTemplate](#capi-tournament-sysdeletetournamenttemplate) - Deletes the tournament template identified by the tournament code.
* [SysCreateDivisionSetConfig](#capi-tournament-syscreatedivisionsetconfig) - Creates a new division set configuration
* [SysDeleteDivisionSetConfig](#capi-tournament-sysdeletedivisionsetconfig) - Deletes the division set configuration uniquely identified by the division set id, with optional, additional enforcement.
* [SysEditDivisionSetConfig](#capi-tournament-syseditdivisionsetconfig) - Updates a division set configuration with specified changes.
* [SysListDivisionSetConfigs](#capi-tournament-syslistdivisionsetconfigs) - Lists all division set configurations for the app.
* [SysReadDivisionSetConfig](#capi-tournament-sysreaddivisionsetconfig) - Reads the current version of the division set configuration identified by the division set id.